<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1181.109521.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Tetranemertes antonina A external appearance of T. antonina, after Buerger (1895) B central stylet of T. antonina after Buerger (1895). Tetranemertes antonina neotype (specimen: TR 3 - DR 23, Museum ID: MNCN 5.02 / 28) C external appearance of living specimen and D head in transmitted light showing distribution and number of ocelli. Abbreviations: ae - anterior end, cg - cerebral ganglion, co - cerebral organ. Scale bars: 4 mm (C); 0.75 mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/916922" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

